        {
          "part": "a",
          "content": "【題目】Using integration by parts, find $\\int x\\sin x\\,dx$.\n\n【解答】Let $u=x$, $dv=\\sin x\\,dx$. Then $du=dx$, $v=-\\cos x$.\n\\[\\int x\\sin x\\,dx=\\int u\\,dv=uv-\\int v\\,du=-x\\cos x+\\int \\cos x\\,dx=-x\\cos x+\\sin x+C.\\]\n\n【知識點】\n- 分部積分選擇：令 $u$ 為多項式（降次），$dv$ 為易積分部分。\n- 自我檢查：對 $-x\\cos x+\\sin x$ 求導應回到 $x\\sin x$。\n\n【常見錯誤】\n- $v=\\int\\sin x\\,dx$ 寫成 $\\cos x$（漏負號）。\n- 忘記常數 $+C$。\n\n【變式練習】\n1) $\\int x\\cos x\\,dx$\n2) $\\int x\\sin(ax)\\,dx$（$a\\ne 0$）\n3) $\\int x^2\\sin x\\,dx$",
          "latex_formulas": [
            "\\int x\\sin x\\,dx",
            "\\int u\\,dv=uv-\\int v\\,du",
            "\\int x\\sin x\\,dx=-x\\cos x+\\sin x+C"
          ],
          "figure_refs": [],
          "marks": null
        },
        {
          "part": "b",
          "content": "【題目】Figure 4 shows the shaded region bounded by the curve $y=\\sqrt{x\\sin x}$ for $0\\le x\\le \\pi$ and the $x$-axis. Find the volume of the solid generated by revolving the region about the $x$-axis. (4 marks)\n\n【解答】Using the disk method,\n\\[V=\\pi\\int_0^{\\pi}y^2\\,dx=\\pi\\int_0^{\\pi}x\\sin x\\,dx.\\]\nUsing (a), $\\int x\\sin x\\,dx=-x\\cos x+\\sin x+C$. Hence\n\\[V=\\pi\\big[-x\\cos x+\\sin x\\big]_0^{\\pi}=\\pi\\big( -\\pi\\cos\\pi+\\sin\\pi - (0)\\big)=\\pi(\\pi)=\\pi^2.\\]\n\n【知識點】\n- 圓盤法：繞 $x$ 軸旋轉，截面面積 $A(x)=\\pi y^2$，所以 $V=\\pi\\int y^2\\,dx$。\n- 本題關鍵：$y=\\sqrt{x\\sin x}$，平方後正好變成 $x\\sin x$，把根號“消掉”。\n\n【常見錯誤】\n- 忘記平方：把 $V$ 寫成 $\\pi\\int y\\,dx$。\n- 上下限寫錯（應為 $0$ 到 $\\pi$）。\n- 帶入端點時把 $\\cos\\pi=-1$ 搞錯。\n\n【變式練習】\n1) $y=\\sqrt{x\\cos x},\\ 0\\le x\\le \\frac{\\pi}{2}$，繞 $x$ 軸旋轉求體積。\n2) 已知 $y=\\sqrt{x\\sin x}$，若改繞 $y$ 軸旋轉，應用哪種方法（殼層/圓盤）？",
          "latex_formulas": [
            "y=\\sqrt{x\\sin x}",
            "V=\\pi\\int_0^{\\pi}y^2\\,dx",
            "V=\\pi\\int_0^{\\pi}x\\sin x\\,dx",
            "V=\\pi\\big[-x\\cos x+\\sin x\\big]_0^{\\pi}=\\pi^2"
          ],
          "figure_refs": [
            "Figure 4"
          ],
          "marks": 4
        }
      ],
